com.cerner.beadledom.guice.dynamicbindings

Class AnnotatedModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.inject.PrivateModule
      • com.cerner.beadledom.guice.dynamicbindings.AnnotatedModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.google.inject.Module

    public abstract class AnnotatedModule
extends com.google.inject.PrivateModule
    A private module associated with a specific binding annotation.

    This module allows binding of DynamicBindingProvider instances for a given type and this modules binding annotation. This is useful for namespacing bindings for library consumers that may be combined within an application and must avoid duplicate bindings. For instance this is useful with beadledom-client so that each service/http client library can have its own namespaced BeadledomClient and feature bindings.

    Note: This module is a private module, so any bindings that should be available to consumers must be exposed via the PrivateModule.expose(com.google.inject.Key<T>) methods. Also, as noted on the DynamicBindingProvider documentation, it is rarely a good idea to expose the dynamic binding provider itself; instead exposing a downstream binding that may use the dynamic binding provider internally.

    Since:
    1.2
    Author:
    John Leacox
